  faq_template_answers_en = [
                  # 'The voicemail app gives you convenient access to all your voice messages from your Telekom landline numbers as well as your mobile access. With the app you no longer have to call your Sprachbox or Mobilbox Pro in order to hear your voicemails - they are pushed straight to your device.',
  #               'You can use Voicemail with SprachBox (IP): If you have an IP-based landline from Telekom, log in to your SprachBox with your Telekom Login.',
  #               'Yes, you can use the app with up to nine devices. Further devices will deactivate the respective first device in the list.',
  #               'To download and use the app is free of charge. If you call someone or send an SMS from within the app, your normal mobile rates apply and you will be charged by your mobile operator. The exact costs are dependent on your contract. Data traffic, such as notifications or the download of messages is billed the same as surfing the internet on your mobile data plan. The additional function "voice recognition" has a free 30 day trial and can be subscribed for 0,99 € per year.',
  #               'Yes, you can receive messages abroad if your smartphone or tablet is connected with the internet via Wi-Fi or mobile network. Please note, however, that this might cause additional roaming costs.',
  #               'The Voicemail App is the update of SprachBox Pro. With Voicemail, you can have access to all your voicemail messages from mobile network and fixed line in a single App. The voice to text feature applies on both SprachBox and MobilBox Pro. This means, with a single booking, you will activate voice to text for both mobile and fixed line messages.',
  #               'To log in use your access number and personal password from the order confirmation of your fixed line access. Alternatively, use your Telekom Login, which you use to access the Kundencenter. Please note that the login will only work with the data of a Telekom IP-based landline access. As user name of your Telekom login, you can enter one of the following options: - Your email-adress@t-online.de - Your Telekom access number - Your mobile phone number that you have associated with your account - Your email address by another provider that you specified during the registration',
  #               'Prerequisite to receive voice messages from your fixed-line access in the app is an IP-based fixed-line access by Telekom. SprachBox is automatically available with such an access. You can login with your Telekom Login. Information about the IP-based access is available at 0800 330 1000, at www.telekom.de or your Telekom Shop.',
  #               'Landline messages are available for 40 days independent of whether they have been read or not whereas new Mobilbox Pro messages are available for 21 days if they are unread and only 7 days if they are read. To keep your messages in the app after this period, you have to archive them through the App.',
  #               'You can share or forward your voice messages with others. If you use the voice recognition function, you have the choice of whether to send only the audio file, the text or both.',
  #               'Please make sure you have allowed push notifications at the first use of the App. If you have disabled push notifications for the Voicemail App you can change this later in the iPhone/iPad settings. If you have set up your @t-online.de email address to forward mails to a different email address, your voice messages are automatically forwarded with them. You will not receive any voicemail in the app this way. The redirect option that can be undone as follows: Open the e-mail center at www.telekom.de/email. There you disable forwarding under Menü > Einstellungen > Weiterleitung.',
                'Depending on the situation, some features might not work, i.e. if an unknown caller leaves a message, as there the caller number is not known, the call back feature does not work. You can recognize disabled features through greyed out buttons.',
                'The greeting is the text that your callers hear when they reach your mailbox. By default the greeting with number is selected, but you can also set a greeting with name or record a personal greeting.',
                'For SprachBox, you can have several personal greetings in order to quickly activate them when needed. To create and manage the greeting for your Mobilbox Pro, please call 3311 from your mobile phone and follow the menu.',
                'Unfortunately, the recording of an annoucement and the activation of the announcement mode is not possible due to technical restrictions.. However, for Sprachbox, you can do it by calling for free the number 08003302424 and dialing 3 then 4 then 4 once in the menu.',
                'You can rename your phone numbers in settings inside the App. When you click on a name, you can rename the number.',
                'Yes, for that, you have to deactivate all call forwarding rules for that number in the settings and delete all messages received on that particular number in the inbox.',
                'You can log out from SprachBox in My numbers. In the list your SprachBox account is listed as "Landline (email@t-online.de)". When you click the three dots to the right, you can log out from the account or remove it completely from the device. For Mobilbox Pro, you have two choices: either you stop being notified on that particular device but Mobilbox Pro can be further used with other devices or you deactivate Mobilbox Pro and retrieve messages through the smartphone native App.',
                "The feature \"Speech recognition\" automatically translates your voice messages to written text. You can see at a glance what the message is about without having to listen to it. This helps to save time and enables you to read the message in situations where you're not able to listen to them - in meetings or in the theater for example. You can try the Speech recognition feature for 30 days for free. Afterwards it can be booked in App Store for 0,99 € per year directly from within the app.",
                'The Speech recognition converts your voice messages automatically to a written text by a machine. Quality highly depends on clear pronunciation. Dialects or languages other than German can not yet be transcribed. Also interference or background noise may affect the translation.',
                'For Sprachbox, you can set in the settings in which cases and after how many seconds your SprachBox answers your calls. For Mobilbox Pro, you have to dial in 3311 and to follow the menu.',
                'The notification function of SprachBox works independent of the app. You can however change that in the settingsr. You can also set the notification setting in the Advanced settings (Settings > At Home > Advanced settings) or at www.telekom.de/telefoniecenter.',
                'This applies when your landline is not available, e.g. when your phone is switched off or during a power outage.',
                'You can set a call forward rule for individual callers for your landline in the settings under "Other landline settings". For Mobilbox Pro, please call 3311 from your mobile phone and follow the menu.'
              ]

